<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="..\config8\suzuki.xsl" ?><!DOCTYPE suzuki [<!ENTITY % sdatacharaents SYSTEM "..\config8\sdatacharaents.txt">%sdatacharaents;]><suzuki><manual>
<section sectnbr = "1G">
<servcat sctnbr = "01" scnbr = "07">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70A1706019" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Sub Fuel Level Sensor Removal and Installation
</title>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Do not touch resister plate (1) and cause deformation of arm (2). It may cause sub fuel level sensor to fail.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70P170014.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "66.314mm" ver = "01" gw = "154" gh = "171"/>
</figure>
</attention2>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A1706019001">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove fuel tank from vehicle. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A1706011"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove fuel pump lock nut (1) from fuel tank (2) using special tool.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L1G015">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09941-51013">
09941–51013
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7V20A171016.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "51.053mm" ver = "01" gw = "137" gh = "128"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Lift sub fuel level sensor (1) slowly and disconnect fuel suction pipe (2) from sub fuel level sensor. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A1706002"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70P170015.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "87.698mm" ver = "01" gw = "171" gh = "232"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove sub fuel level sensor and O-ring from fuel tank.
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A1706019002">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70A1706018">Fuel Level Sensor Inspection</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Clean outside surface of pipe where joint is to be fitted, push joint into pipe until joint lock clicks. And check that pipes are connected securely. Failure to do this may result in fuel leakage.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Clean mating surfaces of fuel pump assembly and fuel tank.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install new O-ring (1) to fuel tank (2).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B170007.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "56.952mm" ver = "01" gw = "199" gh = "145"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect fuel suction pipe (2) to sub fuel level sensor (1).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70P170015.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "87.698mm" ver = "01" gw = "171" gh = "232"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install sub fuel level sensor (1) to fuel tank (2) as follows.
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Align arrow mark (3) on sub fuel level sensor with cutout (4) of fuel tank.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Push sub fuel level sensor down by hand until sub fuel level sensor comes into contact with fuel tank as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B170008.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "90.025mm" ver = "01" gw = "219" gh = "239"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "0.857in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
5.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
O-ring
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
In the state of step b), tighten new fuel pump lock nut (1) by hand.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Use only new fuel pump lock nut. Reusing removed fuel pump lock nut may result in fuel leakage.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
Tighten lock nut while pressing straight on it so that it will not tilt.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A170015.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "60.021mm" ver = "01" gw = "128" gh = "154"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "4" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.291in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "1.291in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
2.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Sub fuel level sensor
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
4.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
O-ring
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
3.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Fuel tank
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Using special tool, tighten fuel pump lock nut (1) until indexes (3) of fuel pump lock nut and fuel tank are aligned.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
Indexes are aligned when fuel pump lock nut is tightened by approx. 1 and 1/3 rotations.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L1G016">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09941-51013">
09941–51013
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7V20A171018.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "89.624mm" ver = "01" gw = "152" gh = "238"/>
</figure>
</s2>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install fuel tank to vehicle. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A1706011"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
